comments.comment_body:
"My name is Ozymandias, King of Kings;
Look on my Works, ye Mighty, and despair!"
--Percy Bysshe Shelley

@Fred Up North (who is "sadly, I don't see a Bill or a Barack in the current crowd.")

Happy not to see those two clowns in the crowd.  The first got us into the 2008 mess by getting rid of Glass-Steagall and the second did very little except for an extremely weak and vulnerable healthcare act despite of having 2 years as a monopoly in DC.

Bernie 2020.  The best, including FDR!

If you think that Iowa is so powerful, review the list of winners in recent decades and see among them: 

Ted Cruz; 
Rick Santorum; 
Mike Huckabee; 
Tom Harkin; 
Richard Gephardt. 

There are four early states. Each in a different region of the country, each with a small enough population for retail politics, selected to represent rural, suburban, African-American, and Hispanic voters.

Even those four don't have anywhere near enough delegates to decide the nominee. We all decide.
